<p class="panel panel-success">Before you can make a user account you need a client.</p>
<p class="panel panel-success">Observations need participants. When creating participants for your client make sure they dont already exist in the system.
You can always edit an existing participant to be registered to more than one client organisation.</p>
<p class="panel panel-success">Most tables allow you to sort information clicking the column name, allowing you to find specific piece of data more quickly.</p>
<p class="panel panel-success">If a client need you to modify some data they entered wrong, start by clicking "List Clients" under Accounts Menu. Then click view details for that client.
This will show you links to all the information related to that client.
Alternatively you can go directly to Sessions or Reports depending on the type of data they want modified.</p>

<h1>Tips for Users</h1>
<p class="panel panel-success">For security reasons, data you create can only be modified afterwards by an Administrator.
